33struct PatternMatchTest : ::testing::Test {
34 LLVMContext Ctx;
35 std::unique_ptr<Module> M;
36 Function *F;
37 BasicBlock *BB;
38 IRBuilder<NoFolder> IRB;
39
40 PatternMatchTest()
41 : M(new Module("PatternMatchTestModule", Ctx)),
42 F(Function::Create(
43 FunctionType::get(Type::getVoidTy(Ctx), /* IsVarArg */ false),
44 Function::ExternalLinkage, "f", M.get())),
45 BB(BasicBlock::Create(Ctx, "entry", F)), IRB(BB) {}
46};
47
48TEST_F(PatternMatchTest, OneUse) {
49 // Build up a little tree of values:
50 //
51 // One = (1 + 2) + 42
52 // Two = One + 42
53 // Leaf = (Two + 8) + (Two + 13)
54 Value *One = IRB.CreateAdd(IRB.CreateAdd(IRB.getInt32(1), IRB.getInt32(2)),
55 IRB.getInt32(42));
56 Value *Two = IRB.CreateAdd(One, IRB.getInt32(42));
57 Value *Leaf = IRB.CreateAdd(IRB.CreateAdd(Two, IRB.getInt32(8)),
58 IRB.CreateAdd(Two, IRB.getInt32(13)));
59 Value *V;
60
61 EXPECT_TRUE(m_OneUse(m_Value(V)).match(One));
62 EXPECT_EQ(One, V);
63
64 EXPECT_FALSE(m_OneUse(m_Value()).match(Two));
65 EXPECT_FALSE(m_OneUse(m_Value()).match(Leaf));
66}

68TEST_F(PatternMatchTest, SpecificIntEQ) {
69 Type *IntTy = IRB.getInt32Ty();
70 unsigned BitWidth = IntTy->getScalarSizeInBits();
71
72 Value *Zero = ConstantInt::get(IntTy, 0);
73 Value *One = ConstantInt::get(IntTy, 1);
74 Value *NegOne = ConstantInt::get(IntTy, -1);
75
76 EXPECT_TRUE(
77 m_SpecificInt_ICMP(ICmpInst::Predicate::ICMP_EQ, APInt(BitWidth, 0))
78 .match(Zero));
79 EXPECT_FALSE(
80 m_SpecificInt_ICMP(ICmpInst::Predicate::ICMP_EQ, APInt(BitWidth, 0))
81 .match(One));
82 EXPECT_FALSE(
83 m_SpecificInt_ICMP(ICmpInst::Predicate::ICMP_EQ, APInt(BitWidth, 0))
84 .match(NegOne));
85
86 EXPECT_FALSE(
87 m_SpecificInt_ICMP(ICmpInst::Predicate::ICMP_EQ, APInt(BitWidth, 1))
88 .match(Zero));
89 EXPECT_TRUE(
90 m_SpecificInt_ICMP(ICmpInst::Predicate::ICMP_EQ, APInt(BitWidth, 1))
91 .match(One));
92 EXPECT_FALSE(
93 m_SpecificInt_ICMP(ICmpInst::Predicate::ICMP_EQ, APInt(BitWidth, 1))
94 .match(NegOne));
95
96 EXPECT_FALSE(
97 m_SpecificInt_ICMP(ICmpInst::Predicate::ICMP_EQ, APInt(BitWidth, -1))
98 .match(Zero));
99 EXPECT_FALSE(
100 m_SpecificInt_ICMP(ICmpInst::Predicate::ICMP_EQ, APInt(BitWidth, -1))
101 .match(One));
102 EXPECT_TRUE(
103 m_SpecificInt_ICMP(ICmpInst::Predicate::ICMP_EQ, APInt(BitWidth, -1))
104 .match(NegOne));
105}

185TEST_F(PatternMatchTest, SignbitZeroChecks) {
186 Type *IntTy = IRB.getInt32Ty();
187
188 Value *Zero = ConstantInt::get(IntTy, 0);
189 Value *One = ConstantInt::get(IntTy, 1);
190 Value *NegOne = ConstantInt::get(IntTy, -1);
191
192 EXPECT_TRUE(m_Negative().match(NegOne));
193 EXPECT_FALSE(m_NonNegative().match(NegOne));
194 EXPECT_FALSE(m_StrictlyPositive().match(NegOne));
195 EXPECT_TRUE(m_NonPositive().match(NegOne));
196
197 EXPECT_FALSE(m_Negative().match(Zero));
198 EXPECT_TRUE(m_NonNegative().match(Zero));
199 EXPECT_FALSE(m_StrictlyPositive().match(Zero));
200 EXPECT_TRUE(m_NonPositive().match(Zero));
201
202 EXPECT_FALSE(m_Negative().match(One));
203 EXPECT_TRUE(m_NonNegative().match(One));
204 EXPECT_TRUE(m_StrictlyPositive().match(One));
205 EXPECT_FALSE(m_NonPositive().match(One));
206}

481TEST_F(PatternMatchTest, Unless) {
482 Value *X = IRB.CreateAdd(IRB.getInt32(1), IRB.getInt32(0));
483
484 EXPECT_TRUE(m_Add(m_One(), m_Zero()).match(X));
485 EXPECT_FALSE(m_Add(m_Zero(), m_One()).match(X));
486
487 EXPECT_FALSE(m_Unless(m_Add(m_One(), m_Zero())).match(X));
488 EXPECT_TRUE(m_Unless(m_Add(m_Zero(), m_One())).match(X));
489
490 EXPECT_TRUE(m_c_Add(m_One(), m_Zero()).match(X));
491 EXPECT_TRUE(m_c_Add(m_Zero(), m_One()).match(X));
492
493 EXPECT_FALSE(m_Unless(m_c_Add(m_One(), m_Zero())).match(X));
494 EXPECT_FALSE(m_Unless(m_c_Add(m_Zero(), m_One())).match(X));
495}

497TEST_F(PatternMatchTest, ZExtSExtSelf) {
498 LLVMContext &Ctx = IRB.getContext();
499
500 Value *One32 = IRB.getInt32(1);
501 Value *One64Z = IRB.CreateZExt(One32, IntegerType::getInt64Ty(Ctx));
502 Value *One64S = IRB.CreateSExt(One32, IntegerType::getInt64Ty(Ctx));
503
504 EXPECT_TRUE(m_One().match(One32));
505 EXPECT_FALSE(m_One().match(One64Z));
506 EXPECT_FALSE(m_One().match(One64S));
507
508 EXPECT_FALSE(m_ZExt(m_One()).match(One32));
509 EXPECT_TRUE(m_ZExt(m_One()).match(One64Z));
510 EXPECT_FALSE(m_ZExt(m_One()).match(One64S));
511
512 EXPECT_FALSE(m_SExt(m_One()).match(One32));
513 EXPECT_FALSE(m_SExt(m_One()).match(One64Z));
514 EXPECT_TRUE(m_SExt(m_One()).match(One64S));
515
516 EXPECT_TRUE(m_ZExtOrSelf(m_One()).match(One32));
517 EXPECT_TRUE(m_ZExtOrSelf(m_One()).match(One64Z));
518 EXPECT_FALSE(m_ZExtOrSelf(m_One()).match(One64S));
519
520 EXPECT_TRUE(m_SExtOrSelf(m_One()).match(One32));
521 EXPECT_FALSE(m_SExtOrSelf(m_One()).match(One64Z));
522 EXPECT_TRUE(m_SExtOrSelf(m_One()).match(One64S));
523
524 EXPECT_FALSE(m_ZExtOrSExt(m_One()).match(One32));
525 EXPECT_TRUE(m_ZExtOrSExt(m_One()).match(One64Z));
526 EXPECT_TRUE(m_ZExtOrSExt(m_One()).match(One64S));
527
528 EXPECT_TRUE(m_ZExtOrSExtOrSelf(m_One()).match(One32));
529 EXPECT_TRUE(m_ZExtOrSExtOrSelf(m_One()).match(One64Z));
530 EXPECT_TRUE(m_ZExtOrSExtOrSelf(m_One()).match(One64S));
531}

533TEST_F(PatternMatchTest, Power2) {
534 Value *C128 = IRB.getInt32(128);
535 Value *CNeg128 = ConstantExpr::getNeg(cast<Constant>(C128));
536
537 EXPECT_TRUE(m_Power2().match(C128));
538 EXPECT_FALSE(m_Power2().match(CNeg128));
539
540 EXPECT_FALSE(m_NegatedPower2().match(C128));
541 EXPECT_TRUE(m_NegatedPower2().match(CNeg128));
542
543 Value *CIntMin = IRB.getInt64(APSInt::getSignedMinValue(64).getSExtValue());
544 Value *CNegIntMin = ConstantExpr::getNeg(cast<Constant>(CIntMin));
545
546 EXPECT_TRUE(m_Power2().match(CIntMin));
547 EXPECT_TRUE(m_Power2().match(CNegIntMin));
548
549 EXPECT_TRUE(m_NegatedPower2().match(CIntMin));
550 EXPECT_TRUE(m_NegatedPower2().match(CNegIntMin));
551}

553TEST_F(PatternMatchTest, CommutativeDeferredValue) {
554 Value *X = IRB.getInt32(1);
555 Value *Y = IRB.getInt32(2);
556
557 {
558 Value *tX = X;
559 EXPECT_TRUE(match(X, m_Deferred(tX)));
560 EXPECT_FALSE(match(Y, m_Deferred(tX)));
561 }
562 {
563 const Value *tX = X;
564 EXPECT_TRUE(match(X, m_Deferred(tX)));
565 EXPECT_FALSE(match(Y, m_Deferred(tX)));
566 }
567 {
568 Value *const tX = X;
569 EXPECT_TRUE(match(X, m_Deferred(tX)));
570 EXPECT_FALSE(match(Y, m_Deferred(tX)));
571 }
572 {
573 const Value *const tX = X;
574 EXPECT_TRUE(match(X, m_Deferred(tX)));
575 EXPECT_FALSE(match(Y, m_Deferred(tX)));
576 }
577
578 {
579 Value *tX = nullptr;
580 EXPECT_TRUE(match(IRB.CreateAnd(X, X), m_And(m_Value(tX), m_Deferred(tX))));
581 EXPECT_EQ(tX, X);
582 }
583 {
584 Value *tX = nullptr;
585 EXPECT_FALSE(
586 match(IRB.CreateAnd(X, Y), m_c_And(m_Value(tX), m_Deferred(tX))));
587 }
588
589 auto checkMatch = [X, Y](Value *Pattern) {
590 Value *tX = nullptr, *tY = nullptr;
591 EXPECT_TRUE(match(
592 Pattern, m_c_And(m_Value(tX), m_c_And(m_Deferred(tX), m_Value(tY)))));
593 EXPECT_EQ(tX, X);
594 EXPECT_EQ(tY, Y);
595 };
596
597 checkMatch(IRB.CreateAnd(X, IRB.CreateAnd(X, Y)));
598 checkMatch(IRB.CreateAnd(X, IRB.CreateAnd(Y, X)));
599 checkMatch(IRB.CreateAnd(IRB.CreateAnd(X, Y), X));
600 checkMatch(IRB.CreateAnd(IRB.CreateAnd(Y, X), X));
601}

603TEST_F(PatternMatchTest, FloatingPointOrderedMin) {
604 Type *FltTy = IRB.getFloatTy();
605 Value *L = ConstantFP::get(FltTy, 1.0);
606 Value *R = ConstantFP::get(FltTy, 2.0);
607 Value *MatchL, *MatchR;
608
609 // Test OLT.
610 EXPECT_TRUE(m_OrdFMin(m_Value(MatchL), m_Value(MatchR))
611 .match(IRB.CreateSelect(IRB.CreateFCmpOLT(L, R), L, R)));
612 EXPECT_EQ(L, MatchL);
613 EXPECT_EQ(R, MatchR);
614
615 // Test OLE.
616 EXPECT_TRUE(m_OrdFMin(m_Value(MatchL), m_Value(MatchR))
617 .match(IRB.CreateSelect(IRB.CreateFCmpOLE(L, R), L, R)));
618 EXPECT_EQ(L, MatchL);
619 EXPECT_EQ(R, MatchR);
620
621 // Test no match on OGE.
622 EXPECT_FALSE(m_OrdFMin(m_Value(MatchL), m_Value(MatchR))
623 .match(IRB.CreateSelect(IRB.CreateFCmpOGE(L, R), L, R)));
624
625 // Test no match on OGT.
626 EXPECT_FALSE(m_OrdFMin(m_Value(MatchL), m_Value(MatchR))
627 .match(IRB.CreateSelect(IRB.CreateFCmpOGT(L, R), L, R)));
628
629 // Test inverted selects. Note, that this "inverts" the ordering, e.g.:
630 // %cmp = fcmp oge L, R
631 // %min = select %cmp R, L
632 // Given L == NaN
633 // the above is expanded to %cmp == false ==> %min = L
634 // which is true for UnordFMin, not OrdFMin, so test that:
635
636 // [OU]GE with inverted select.
637 EXPECT_FALSE(m_OrdFMin(m_Value(MatchL), m_Value(MatchR))
638 .match(IRB.CreateSelect(IRB.CreateFCmpOGE(L, R), R, L)));
639 EXPECT_TRUE(m_OrdFMin(m_Value(MatchL), m_Value(MatchR))
640 .match(IRB.CreateSelect(IRB.CreateFCmpUGE(L, R), R, L)));
641 EXPECT_EQ(L, MatchL);
642 EXPECT_EQ(R, MatchR);
643
644 // [OU]GT with inverted select.
645 EXPECT_FALSE(m_OrdFMin(m_Value(MatchL), m_Value(MatchR))
646 .match(IRB.CreateSelect(IRB.CreateFCmpOGT(L, R), R, L)));
647 EXPECT_TRUE(m_OrdFMin(m_Value(MatchL), m_Value(MatchR))
648 .match(IRB.CreateSelect(IRB.CreateFCmpUGT(L, R), R, L)));
649 EXPECT_EQ(L, MatchL);
650 EXPECT_EQ(R, MatchR);
651}

804TEST_F(PatternMatchTest, OverflowingBinOps) {
805 Value *L = IRB.getInt32(1);
806 Value *R = IRB.getInt32(2);
807 Value *MatchL, *MatchR;
808
809 EXPECT_TRUE(
810 m_NSWAdd(m_Value(MatchL), m_Value(MatchR)).match(IRB.CreateNSWAdd(L, R)));
811 EXPECT_EQ(L, MatchL);
812 EXPECT_EQ(R, MatchR);
813 MatchL = MatchR = nullptr;
814 EXPECT_TRUE(
815 m_NSWSub(m_Value(MatchL), m_Value(MatchR)).match(IRB.CreateNSWSub(L, R)));
816 EXPECT_EQ(L, MatchL);
817 EXPECT_EQ(R, MatchR);
818 MatchL = MatchR = nullptr;
819 EXPECT_TRUE(
820 m_NSWMul(m_Value(MatchL), m_Value(MatchR)).match(IRB.CreateNSWMul(L, R)));
821 EXPECT_EQ(L, MatchL);
822 EXPECT_EQ(R, MatchR);
823 MatchL = MatchR = nullptr;
824 EXPECT_TRUE(m_NSWShl(m_Value(MatchL), m_Value(MatchR)).match(
825 IRB.CreateShl(L, R, "", /* NUW */ false, /* NSW */ true)));
826 EXPECT_EQ(L, MatchL);
827 EXPECT_EQ(R, MatchR);
828
829 EXPECT_TRUE(
830 m_NUWAdd(m_Value(MatchL), m_Value(MatchR)).match(IRB.CreateNUWAdd(L, R)));
831 EXPECT_EQ(L, MatchL);
832 EXPECT_EQ(R, MatchR);
833 MatchL = MatchR = nullptr;
834 EXPECT_TRUE(
835 m_NUWSub(m_Value(MatchL), m_Value(MatchR)).match(IRB.CreateNUWSub(L, R)));
836 EXPECT_EQ(L, MatchL);
837 EXPECT_EQ(R, MatchR);
838 MatchL = MatchR = nullptr;
839 EXPECT_TRUE(
840 m_NUWMul(m_Value(MatchL), m_Value(MatchR)).match(IRB.CreateNUWMul(L, R)));
841 EXPECT_EQ(L, MatchL);
842 EXPECT_EQ(R, MatchR);
843 MatchL = MatchR = nullptr;
844 EXPECT_TRUE(m_NUWShl(m_Value(MatchL), m_Value(MatchR)).match(
845 IRB.CreateShl(L, R, "", /* NUW */ true, /* NSW */ false)));
846 EXPECT_EQ(L, MatchL);
847 EXPECT_EQ(R, MatchR);
848
849 EXPECT_FALSE(m_NSWAdd(m_Value(), m_Value()).match(IRB.CreateAdd(L, R)));
850 EXPECT_FALSE(m_NSWAdd(m_Value(), m_Value()).match(IRB.CreateNUWAdd(L, R)));
851 EXPECT_FALSE(m_NSWAdd(m_Value(), m_Value()).match(IRB.CreateNSWSub(L, R)));
852 EXPECT_FALSE(m_NSWSub(m_Value(), m_Value()).match(IRB.CreateSub(L, R)));
853 EXPECT_FALSE(m_NSWSub(m_Value(), m_Value()).match(IRB.CreateNUWSub(L, R)));
854 EXPECT_FALSE(m_NSWSub(m_Value(), m_Value()).match(IRB.CreateNSWAdd(L, R)));
855 EXPECT_FALSE(m_NSWMul(m_Value(), m_Value()).match(IRB.CreateMul(L, R)));
856 EXPECT_FALSE(m_NSWMul(m_Value(), m_Value()).match(IRB.CreateNUWMul(L, R)));
857 EXPECT_FALSE(m_NSWMul(m_Value(), m_Value()).match(IRB.CreateNSWAdd(L, R)));
858 EXPECT_FALSE(m_NSWShl(m_Value(), m_Value()).match(IRB.CreateShl(L, R)));
859 EXPECT_FALSE(m_NSWShl(m_Value(), m_Value()).match(
860 IRB.CreateShl(L, R, "", /* NUW */ true, /* NSW */ false)));
861 EXPECT_FALSE(m_NSWShl(m_Value(), m_Value()).match(IRB.CreateNSWAdd(L, R)));
862
863 EXPECT_FALSE(m_NUWAdd(m_Value(), m_Value()).match(IRB.CreateAdd(L, R)));
864 EXPECT_FALSE(m_NUWAdd(m_Value(), m_Value()).match(IRB.CreateNSWAdd(L, R)));
865 EXPECT_FALSE(m_NUWAdd(m_Value(), m_Value()).match(IRB.CreateNUWSub(L, R)));
866 EXPECT_FALSE(m_NUWSub(m_Value(), m_Value()).match(IRB.CreateSub(L, R)));

878TEST_F(PatternMatchTest, LoadStoreOps) {
879 // Create this load/store sequence:
880 //
881 // %p = alloca i32*
882 // %0 = load i32*, i32** %p
883 // store i32 42, i32* %0
884
885 Value *Alloca = IRB.CreateAlloca(IRB.getInt32Ty());
886 Value *LoadInst = IRB.CreateLoad(IRB.getInt32Ty(), Alloca);
887 Value *FourtyTwo = IRB.getInt32(42);
888 Value *StoreInst = IRB.CreateStore(FourtyTwo, Alloca);
889 Value *MatchLoad, *MatchStoreVal, *MatchStorePointer;
890
891 EXPECT_TRUE(m_Load(m_Value(MatchLoad)).match(LoadInst));
892 EXPECT_EQ(Alloca, MatchLoad);
893
894 EXPECT_TRUE(m_Load(m_Specific(Alloca)).match(LoadInst));
895
896 EXPECT_FALSE(m_Load(m_Value(MatchLoad)).match(Alloca));
897
898 EXPECT_TRUE(m_Store(m_Value(MatchStoreVal), m_Value(MatchStorePointer))
899 .match(StoreInst));
900 EXPECT_EQ(FourtyTwo, MatchStoreVal);
901 EXPECT_EQ(Alloca, MatchStorePointer);
902
903 EXPECT_FALSE(m_Store(m_Value(MatchStoreVal), m_Value(MatchStorePointer))
904 .match(Alloca));
905
906 EXPECT_TRUE(m_Store(m_SpecificInt(42), m_Specific(Alloca))
907 .match(StoreInst));
908 EXPECT_FALSE(m_Store(m_SpecificInt(42), m_Specific(FourtyTwo))
909 .match(StoreInst));
910 EXPECT_FALSE(m_Store(m_SpecificInt(43), m_Specific(Alloca))
911 .match(StoreInst));
912}

914TEST_F(PatternMatchTest, VectorOps) {
915 // Build up small tree of vector operations
916 //
917 // Val = 0 + 1
918 // Val2 = Val + 3
919 // VI1 = insertelement <2 x i8> undef, i8 1, i32 0 = <1, undef>
920 // VI2 = insertelement <2 x i8> %VI1, i8 %Val2, i8 %Val = <1, 4>
921 // VI3 = insertelement <2 x i8> %VI1, i8 %Val2, i32 1 = <1, 4>
922 // VI4 = insertelement <2 x i8> %VI1, i8 2, i8 %Val = <1, 2>
923 //
924 // SI1 = shufflevector <2 x i8> %VI1, <2 x i8> undef, zeroinitializer
925 // SI2 = shufflevector <2 x i8> %VI3, <2 x i8> %VI4, <2 x i8> <i8 0, i8 2>
926 // SI3 = shufflevector <2 x i8> %VI3, <2 x i8> undef, zeroinitializer
927 // SI4 = shufflevector <2 x i8> %VI4, <2 x i8> undef, zeroinitializer
928 //
929 // SP1 = VectorSplat(2, i8 2)
930 // SP2 = VectorSplat(2, i8 %Val)
931 Type *VecTy = FixedVectorType::get(IRB.getInt8Ty(), 2);
932 Type *i32 = IRB.getInt32Ty();
933 Type *i32VecTy = FixedVectorType::get(i32, 2);
934
935 Value *Val = IRB.CreateAdd(IRB.getInt8(0), IRB.getInt8(1));
936 Value *Val2 = IRB.CreateAdd(Val, IRB.getInt8(3));
937
938 SmallVector<Constant *, 2> VecElemIdxs;
939 VecElemIdxs.push_back(ConstantInt::get(i32, 0));
940 VecElemIdxs.push_back(ConstantInt::get(i32, 2));
941 auto *IdxVec = ConstantVector::get(VecElemIdxs);
942
943 Value *UndefVec = UndefValue::get(VecTy);
944 Value *VI1 = IRB.CreateInsertElement(UndefVec, IRB.getInt8(1), (uint64_t)0);
945 Value *VI2 = IRB.CreateInsertElement(VI1, Val2, Val);
946 Value *VI3 = IRB.CreateInsertElement(VI1, Val2, (uint64_t)1);
947 Value *VI4 = IRB.CreateInsertElement(VI1, IRB.getInt8(2), Val);
948
949 Value *EX1 = IRB.CreateExtractElement(VI4, Val);
950 Value *EX2 = IRB.CreateExtractElement(VI4, (uint64_t)0);
951 Value *EX3 = IRB.CreateExtractElement(IdxVec, (uint64_t)1);
952
953 Constant *Zero = ConstantAggregateZero::get(i32VecTy);
954 SmallVector<int, 16> ZeroMask;
955 ShuffleVectorInst::getShuffleMask(Zero, ZeroMask);
956
957 Value *SI1 = IRB.CreateShuffleVector(VI1, ZeroMask);
958 Value *SI2 = IRB.CreateShuffleVector(VI3, VI4, IdxVec);
959 Value *SI3 = IRB.CreateShuffleVector(VI3, ZeroMask);
960 Value *SI4 = IRB.CreateShuffleVector(VI4, ZeroMask);
961
962 Value *SP1 = IRB.CreateVectorSplat(2, IRB.getInt8(2));
963 Value *SP2 = IRB.CreateVectorSplat(2, Val);
964
965 Value *A = nullptr, *B = nullptr, *C = nullptr;
966
967 // Test matching insertelement
968 EXPECT_TRUE(match(VI1, m_InsertElt(m_Value(), m_Value(), m_Value())));
969 EXPECT_TRUE(
970 match(VI1, m_InsertElt(m_Undef(), m_ConstantInt(), m_ConstantInt())));
971 EXPECT_TRUE(
972 match(VI1, m_InsertElt(m_Undef(), m_ConstantInt(), m_Zero())));
973 EXPECT_TRUE(
974 match(VI1, m_InsertElt(m_Undef(), m_SpecificInt(1), m_Zero())));
975 EXPECT_TRUE(match(VI2, m_InsertElt(m_Value(), m_Value(), m_Value())));
976 EXPECT_FALSE(
977 match(VI2, m_InsertElt(m_Value(), m_Value(), m_ConstantInt())));
978 EXPECT_FALSE(
979 match(VI2, m_InsertElt(m_Value(), m_ConstantInt(), m_Value())));
980 EXPECT_FALSE(match(VI2, m_InsertElt(m_Constant(), m_Value(), m_Value())));
981 EXPECT_TRUE(match(VI3, m_InsertElt(m_Value(A), m_Value(B), m_Value(C))));
982 EXPECT_TRUE(A == VI1);
983 EXPECT_TRUE(B == Val2);
984 EXPECT_TRUE(isa<ConstantInt>(C));
985 A = B = C = nullptr; // reset
986
987 // Test matching extractelement
988 EXPECT_TRUE(match(EX1, m_ExtractElt(m_Value(A), m_Value(B))));
989 EXPECT_TRUE(A == VI4);
990 EXPECT_TRUE(B == Val);
991 A = B = C = nullptr; // reset
992 EXPECT_FALSE(match(EX1, m_ExtractElt(m_Value(), m_ConstantInt())));
993 EXPECT_TRUE(match(EX2, m_ExtractElt(m_Value(), m_ConstantInt())));
994 EXPECT_TRUE(match(EX3, m_ExtractElt(m_Constant(), m_ConstantInt())));
995
996 // Test matching shufflevector
997 ArrayRef<int> Mask;
998 EXPECT_TRUE(match(SI1, m_Shuffle(m_Value(), m_Undef(), m_ZeroMask())));
999 EXPECT_TRUE(match(SI2, m_Shuffle(m_Value(A), m_Value(B), m_Mask(Mask))));
1000 EXPECT_TRUE(A == VI3);
1001 EXPECT_TRUE(B == VI4);
1002 A = B = C = nullptr; // reset
1003
1004 // Test matching the vector splat pattern
1005 EXPECT_TRUE(match(
1006 SI1,
1007 m_Shuffle(m_InsertElt(m_Undef(), m_SpecificInt(1), m_Zero()),
1008 m_Undef(), m_ZeroMask())));
1009 EXPECT_FALSE(match(
1010 SI3, m_Shuffle(m_InsertElt(m_Undef(), m_Value(), m_Zero()),
1011 m_Undef(), m_ZeroMask())));
1012 EXPECT_FALSE(match(
1013 SI4, m_Shuffle(m_InsertElt(m_Undef(), m_Value(), m_Zero()),
1014 m_Undef(), m_ZeroMask())));
1015 EXPECT_TRUE(match(
1016 SP1,
1017 m_Shuffle(m_InsertElt(m_Undef(), m_SpecificInt(2), m_Zero()),
1018 m_Undef(), m_ZeroMask())));
1019 EXPECT_TRUE(match(
1020 SP2, m_Shuffle(m_InsertElt(m_Undef(), m_Value(A), m_Zero()),
1021 m_Undef(), m_ZeroMask())));
1022 EXPECT_TRUE(A == Val);
1023}

1025TEST_F(PatternMatchTest, VectorUndefInt) {
1026 Type *ScalarTy = IRB.getInt8Ty();
1027 Type *VectorTy = FixedVectorType::get(ScalarTy, 4);
1028 Constant *ScalarUndef = UndefValue::get(ScalarTy);
1029 Constant *VectorUndef = UndefValue::get(VectorTy);
1030 Constant *ScalarZero = Constant::getNullValue(ScalarTy);
1031 Constant *VectorZero = Constant::getNullValue(VectorTy);
1032
1033 SmallVector<Constant *, 4> Elems;
1034 Elems.push_back(ScalarUndef);
1035 Elems.push_back(ScalarZero);
1036 Elems.push_back(ScalarUndef);
1037 Elems.push_back(ScalarZero);
1038 Constant *VectorZeroUndef = ConstantVector::get(Elems);
1039
1040 EXPECT_TRUE(match(ScalarUndef, m_Undef()));
1041 EXPECT_TRUE(match(VectorUndef, m_Undef()));
1042 EXPECT_FALSE(match(ScalarZero, m_Undef()));
1043 EXPECT_FALSE(match(VectorZero, m_Undef()));
1044 EXPECT_FALSE(match(VectorZeroUndef, m_Undef()));
1045
1046 EXPECT_FALSE(match(ScalarUndef, m_Zero()));
1047 EXPECT_FALSE(match(VectorUndef, m_Zero()));
1048 EXPECT_TRUE(match(ScalarZero, m_Zero()));
1049 EXPECT_TRUE(match(VectorZero, m_Zero()));
1050 EXPECT_TRUE(match(VectorZeroUndef, m_Zero()));
1051
1052 const APInt *C;
1053 // Regardless of whether undefs are allowed,
1054 // a fully undef constant does not match.
1055 EXPECT_FALSE(match(ScalarUndef, m_APInt(C)));
1056 EXPECT_FALSE(match(ScalarUndef, m_APIntForbidUndef(C)));
1057 EXPECT_FALSE(match(ScalarUndef, m_APIntAllowUndef(C)));
1058 EXPECT_FALSE(match(VectorUndef, m_APInt(C)));
1059 EXPECT_FALSE(match(VectorUndef, m_APIntForbidUndef(C)));
1060 EXPECT_FALSE(match(VectorUndef, m_APIntAllowUndef(C)));
1061
1062 // We can always match simple constants and simple splats.
1063 C = nullptr;
1064 EXPECT_TRUE(match(ScalarZero, m_APInt(C)));
1065 EXPECT_TRUE(C->isNullValue());
1066 C = nullptr;
1067 EXPECT_TRUE(match(ScalarZero, m_APIntForbidUndef(C)));
1068 EXPECT_TRUE(C->isNullValue());
1069 C = nullptr;
1070 EXPECT_TRUE(match(ScalarZero, m_APIntAllowUndef(C)));
1071 EXPECT_TRUE(C->isNullValue());
1072 C = nullptr;
1073 EXPECT_TRUE(match(VectorZero, m_APInt(C)));
1074 EXPECT_TRUE(C->isNullValue());
1075 C = nullptr;
1076 EXPECT_TRUE(match(VectorZero, m_APIntForbidUndef(C)));
1077 EXPECT_TRUE(C->isNullValue());
1078 C = nullptr;
1079 EXPECT_TRUE(match(VectorZero, m_APIntAllowUndef(C)));
1080 EXPECT_TRUE(C->isNullValue());
1081
1082 // Whether splats with undef can be matched depends on the matcher.
1083 EXPECT_FALSE(match(VectorZeroUndef, m_APInt(C)));
1084 EXPECT_FALSE(match(VectorZeroUndef, m_APIntForbidUndef(C)));
1085 C = nullptr;
1086 EXPECT_TRUE(match(VectorZeroUndef, m_APIntAllowUndef(C)));
1087 EXPECT_TRUE(C->isNullValue());
1088}

1212TEST_F(PatternMatchTest, FloatingPointFNeg) {
1213 Type *FltTy = IRB.getFloatTy();
1214 Value *One = ConstantFP::get(FltTy, 1.0);
1215 Value *Z = ConstantFP::get(FltTy, 0.0);
1216 Value *NZ = ConstantFP::get(FltTy, -0.0);
1217 Value *V = IRB.CreateFNeg(One);
1218 Value *V1 = IRB.CreateFSub(NZ, One);
1219 Value *V2 = IRB.CreateFSub(Z, One);
1220 Value *V3 = IRB.CreateFAdd(NZ, One);
1221 Value *Match;
1222
1223 // Test FNeg(1.0)
1224 EXPECT_TRUE(match(V, m_FNeg(m_Value(Match))));
1225 EXPECT_EQ(One, Match);
1226
1227 // Test FSub(-0.0, 1.0)
1228 EXPECT_TRUE(match(V1, m_FNeg(m_Value(Match))));
1229 EXPECT_EQ(One, Match);
1230
1231 // Test FSub(0.0, 1.0)
1232 EXPECT_FALSE(match(V2, m_FNeg(m_Value(Match))));
1233 cast<Instruction>(V2)->setHasNoSignedZeros(true);
1234 EXPECT_TRUE(match(V2, m_FNeg(m_Value(Match))));
1235 EXPECT_EQ(One, Match);
1236
1237 // Test FAdd(-0.0, 1.0)
1238 EXPECT_FALSE(match(V3, m_FNeg(m_Value(Match))));
1239}

1241TEST_F(PatternMatchTest, CondBranchTest) {
1242 BasicBlock *TrueBB = BasicBlock::Create(Ctx, "TrueBB", F);
1243 BasicBlock *FalseBB = BasicBlock::Create(Ctx, "FalseBB", F);
1244 Value *Br1 = IRB.CreateCondBr(IRB.getTrue(), TrueBB, FalseBB);
1245
1246 EXPECT_TRUE(match(Br1, m_Br(m_Value(), m_BasicBlock(), m_BasicBlock())));
1247
1248 BasicBlock *A, *B;
1249 EXPECT_TRUE(match(Br1, m_Br(m_Value(), m_BasicBlock(A), m_BasicBlock(B))));
1250 EXPECT_EQ(TrueBB, A);
1251 EXPECT_EQ(FalseBB, B);
1252
1253 EXPECT_FALSE(
1254 match(Br1, m_Br(m_Value(), m_SpecificBB(FalseBB), m_BasicBlock())));
1255 EXPECT_FALSE(
1256 match(Br1, m_Br(m_Value(), m_BasicBlock(), m_SpecificBB(TrueBB))));
1257 EXPECT_FALSE(
1258 match(Br1, m_Br(m_Value(), m_SpecificBB(FalseBB), m_BasicBlock(TrueBB))));
1259 EXPECT_TRUE(
1260 match(Br1, m_Br(m_Value(), m_SpecificBB(TrueBB), m_BasicBlock(FalseBB))));
1261
1262 // Check we can use m_Deferred with branches.
1263 EXPECT_FALSE(match(Br1, m_Br(m_Value(), m_BasicBlock(A), m_Deferred(A))));
1264 Value *Br2 = IRB.CreateCondBr(IRB.getTrue(), TrueBB, TrueBB);
1265 A = nullptr;
1266 EXPECT_TRUE(match(Br2, m_Br(m_Value(), m_BasicBlock(A), m_Deferred(A))));
1267}

1269TEST_F(PatternMatchTest, WithOverflowInst) {
1270 Value *Add = IRB.CreateBinaryIntrinsic(Intrinsic::uadd_with_overflow,
1271 IRB.getInt32(0), IRB.getInt32(0));
1272 Value *Add0 = IRB.CreateExtractValue(Add, 0);
1273 Value *Add1 = IRB.CreateExtractValue(Add, 1);
1274
1275 EXPECT_TRUE(match(Add0, m_ExtractValue<0>(m_Value())));
1276 EXPECT_FALSE(match(Add0, m_ExtractValue<1>(m_Value())));
1277 EXPECT_FALSE(match(Add1, m_ExtractValue<0>(m_Value())));
1278 EXPECT_TRUE(match(Add1, m_ExtractValue<1>(m_Value())));
1279 EXPECT_FALSE(match(Add, m_ExtractValue<1>(m_Value())));
1280 EXPECT_FALSE(match(Add, m_ExtractValue<1>(m_Value())));
1281
1282 WithOverflowInst *WOI;
1283 EXPECT_FALSE(match(Add0, m_WithOverflowInst(WOI)));
1284 EXPECT_FALSE(match(Add1, m_WithOverflowInst(WOI)));
1285 EXPECT_TRUE(match(Add, m_WithOverflowInst(WOI)));
1286
1287 EXPECT_TRUE(match(Add0, m_ExtractValue<0>(m_WithOverflowInst(WOI))));
1288 EXPECT_EQ(Add, WOI);
1289 EXPECT_TRUE(match(Add1, m_ExtractValue<1>(m_WithOverflowInst(WOI))));
1290 EXPECT_EQ(Add, WOI);
1291}

1293TEST_F(PatternMatchTest, MinMaxIntrinsics) {
1294 Type *Ty = IRB.getInt32Ty();
1295 Value *L = ConstantInt::get(Ty, 1);
1296 Value *R = ConstantInt::get(Ty, 2);
1297 Value *MatchL, *MatchR;
1298
1299 // Check for intrinsic ID match and capture of operands.
1300 EXPECT_TRUE(m_SMax(m_Value(MatchL), m_Value(MatchR))
1301 .match(IRB.CreateBinaryIntrinsic(Intrinsic::smax, L, R)));
1302 EXPECT_EQ(L, MatchL);
1303 EXPECT_EQ(R, MatchR);
1304
1305 EXPECT_TRUE(m_SMin(m_Value(MatchL), m_Value(MatchR))
1306 .match(IRB.CreateBinaryIntrinsic(Intrinsic::smin, L, R)));
1307 EXPECT_EQ(L, MatchL);
1308 EXPECT_EQ(R, MatchR);
1309
1310 EXPECT_TRUE(m_UMax(m_Value(MatchL), m_Value(MatchR))
1311 .match(IRB.CreateBinaryIntrinsic(Intrinsic::umax, L, R)));
1312 EXPECT_EQ(L, MatchL);
1313 EXPECT_EQ(R, MatchR);
1314
1315 EXPECT_TRUE(m_UMin(m_Value(MatchL), m_Value(MatchR))
1316 .match(IRB.CreateBinaryIntrinsic(Intrinsic::umin, L, R)));
1317 EXPECT_EQ(L, MatchL);
1318 EXPECT_EQ(R, MatchR);
1319
1320 // Check for intrinsic ID mismatch.
1321 EXPECT_FALSE(m_SMax(m_Value(MatchL), m_Value(MatchR))
1322 .match(IRB.CreateBinaryIntrinsic(Intrinsic::smin, L, R)));
1323 EXPECT_FALSE(m_SMin(m_Value(MatchL), m_Value(MatchR))
1324 .match(IRB.CreateBinaryIntrinsic(Intrinsic::umax, L, R)));
1325 EXPECT_FALSE(m_UMax(m_Value(MatchL), m_Value(MatchR))
1326 .match(IRB.CreateBinaryIntrinsic(Intrinsic::umin, L, R)));
1327 EXPECT_FALSE(m_UMin(m_Value(MatchL), m_Value(MatchR))
1328 .match(IRB.CreateBinaryIntrinsic(Intrinsic::smax, L, R)));
1329}

1331TEST_F(PatternMatchTest, IntrinsicMatcher) {
1332 Value *Name = IRB.CreateAlloca(IRB.getInt8Ty());
1333 Value *Hash = IRB.getInt64(0);
1334 Value *Num = IRB.getInt32(1);
1335 Value *Index = IRB.getInt32(2);
1336 Value *Step = IRB.getInt64(3);
1337
1338 Value *Ops[] = {Name, Hash, Num, Index, Step};
1339 Module *M = BB->getParent()->getParent();
1340 Function *TheFn =
1341 Intrinsic::getDeclaration(M, Intrinsic::instrprof_increment_step);
1342
1343 Value *Intrinsic5 = CallInst::Create(TheFn, Ops, "", BB);
1344
1345 // Match without capturing.
1346 EXPECT_TRUE(match(
1347 Intrinsic5, m_Intrinsic<Intrinsic::instrprof_increment_step>(
1348 m_Value(), m_Value(), m_Value(), m_Value(), m_Value())));
1349 EXPECT_FALSE(match(
1350 Intrinsic5, m_Intrinsic<Intrinsic::memmove>(
1351 m_Value(), m_Value(), m_Value(), m_Value(), m_Value())));
1352
1353 // Match with capturing.
1354 Value *Arg1 = nullptr;
1355 Value *Arg2 = nullptr;
1356 Value *Arg3 = nullptr;
1357 Value *Arg4 = nullptr;
1358 Value *Arg5 = nullptr;
1359 EXPECT_TRUE(
1360 match(Intrinsic5, m_Intrinsic<Intrinsic::instrprof_increment_step>(
1361 m_Value(Arg1), m_Value(Arg2), m_Value(Arg3),
1362 m_Value(Arg4), m_Value(Arg5))));
1363 EXPECT_EQ(Arg1, Name);
1364 EXPECT_EQ(Arg2, Hash);
1365 EXPECT_EQ(Arg3, Num);
1366 EXPECT_EQ(Arg4, Index);
1367 EXPECT_EQ(Arg5, Step);
1368
1369 // Match specific second argument.
1370 EXPECT_TRUE(
1371 match(Intrinsic5,
1372 m_Intrinsic<Intrinsic::instrprof_increment_step>(
1373 m_Value(), m_SpecificInt(0), m_Value(), m_Value(), m_Value())));
1374 EXPECT_FALSE(
1375 match(Intrinsic5, m_Intrinsic<Intrinsic::instrprof_increment_step>(
1376 m_Value(), m_SpecificInt(10), m_Value(), m_Value(),
1377 m_Value())));
1378
1379 // Match specific third argument.
1380 EXPECT_TRUE(
1381 match(Intrinsic5,
1382 m_Intrinsic<Intrinsic::instrprof_increment_step>(
1383 m_Value(), m_Value(), m_SpecificInt(1), m_Value(), m_Value())));
1384 EXPECT_FALSE(
1385 match(Intrinsic5, m_Intrinsic<Intrinsic::instrprof_increment_step>(
1386 m_Value(), m_Value(), m_SpecificInt(10), m_Value(),
1387 m_Value())));
1388
1389 // Match specific fourth argument.
1390 EXPECT_TRUE(
1391 match(Intrinsic5,
1392 m_Intrinsic<Intrinsic::instrprof_increment_step>(
1393 m_Value(), m_Value(), m_Value(), m_SpecificInt(2), m_Value())));
1394 EXPECT_FALSE(
1395 match(Intrinsic5, m_Intrinsic<Intrinsic::instrprof_increment_step>(
1396 m_Value(), m_Value(), m_Value(), m_SpecificInt(10),
1397 m_Value())));
1398
1399 // Match specific fifth argument.
1400 EXPECT_TRUE(
1401 match(Intrinsic5,
1402 m_Intrinsic<Intrinsic::instrprof_increment_step>(
1403 m_Value(), m_Value(), m_Value(), m_Value(), m_SpecificInt(3))));
1404 EXPECT_FALSE(
1405 match(Intrinsic5, m_Intrinsic<Intrinsic::instrprof_increment_step>(
1406 m_Value(), m_Value(), m_Value(), m_Value(),
1407 m_SpecificInt(10))));
1408}

1410namespace {
1411
1412struct is_unsigned_zero_pred {
1413 bool isValue(const APInt &C) { return C.isNullValue(); }
1414};
1415
1416struct is_float_zero_pred {
1417 bool isValue(const APFloat &C) { return C.isZero(); }
1418};
1419
1420template <typename T> struct always_true_pred {
1421 bool isValue(const T &) { return true; }
1422};
1423
1424template <typename T> struct always_false_pred {
1425 bool isValue(const T &) { return false; }
1426};
1427
1428struct is_unsigned_max_pred {
1429 bool isValue(const APInt &C) { return C.isMaxValue(); }
1430};
1431
1432struct is_float_nan_pred {
1433 bool isValue(const APFloat &C) { return C.isNaN(); }
1434};
1435
1436} // namespace

1438TEST_F(PatternMatchTest, ConstantPredicateType) {
1439
1440 // Scalar integer
1441 APInt U32Max = APInt::getAllOnesValue(32);
1442 APInt U32Zero = APInt::getNullValue(32);
1443 APInt U32DeadBeef(32, 0xDEADBEEF);
1444
1445 Type *U32Ty = Type::getInt32Ty(Ctx);
1446
1447 Constant *CU32Max = Constant::getIntegerValue(U32Ty, U32Max);
1448 Constant *CU32Zero = Constant::getIntegerValue(U32Ty, U32Zero);

1451 EXPECT_TRUE(match(CU32Max, cst_pred_ty<is_unsigned_max_pred>()));
1452 EXPECT_FALSE(match(CU32Max, cst_pred_ty<is_unsigned_zero_pred>()));

1454 EXPECT_FALSE(match(CU32Max, cst_pred_ty<always_false_pred<APInt>>()));
1455

1457 EXPECT_TRUE(match(CU32Zero, cst_pred_ty<is_unsigned_zero_pred>()));

1459 EXPECT_FALSE(match(CU32Zero, cst_pred_ty<always_false_pred<APInt>>()));

1461 EXPECT_FALSE(match(CU32DeadBeef, cst_pred_ty<is_unsigned_max_pred>()));
1462 EXPECT_FALSE(match(CU32DeadBeef, cst_pred_ty<is_unsigned_zero_pred>()));
1463 EXPECT_TRUE(match(CU32DeadBeef, cst_pred_ty<always_true_pred<APInt>>()));

1468 APFloat F32Zero = APFloat::getZero(APFloat::IEEEsingle());

1480 EXPECT_FALSE(match(CF32NaN, cstfp_pred_ty<always_false_pred<APFloat>>()));

1483 EXPECT_TRUE(match(CF32Zero, cstfp_pred_ty<is_float_zero_pred>()));
1484 EXPECT_TRUE(match(CF32Zero, cstfp_pred_ty<always_true_pred<APFloat>>()));
1485 EXPECT_FALSE(match(CF32Zero, cstfp_pred_ty<always_false_pred<APFloat>>()));

1488 EXPECT_FALSE(match(CF32Pi, cstfp_pred_ty<is_float_zero_pred>()));
1489 EXPECT_TRUE(match(CF32Pi, cstfp_pred_ty<always_true_pred<APFloat>>()));
1490 EXPECT_FALSE(match(CF32Pi, cstfp_pred_ty<always_false_pred<APFloat>>()));
1491

1493 auto ScalableEC = ElementCount::getScalable(4);
1494

1496
1497 for (auto EC : {FixedEC, ScalableEC}) {

1510 EXPECT_TRUE(match(CSplatU32Zero, cst_pred_ty<is_unsigned_zero_pred>()));
1511 EXPECT_TRUE(match(CSplatU32Zero, cst_pred_ty<always_true_pred<APInt>>()));
1512 EXPECT_FALSE(match(CSplatU32Zero, cst_pred_ty<always_false_pred<APInt>>()));

1518 match(CSplatU32DeadBeef, cst_pred_ty<always_true_pred<APInt>>()));

1534
1535 EXPECT_FALSE(match(CSplatF32Zero, cstfp_pred_ty<is_float_nan_pred>()));
1536 EXPECT_TRUE(match(CSplatF32Zero, cstfp_pred_ty<is_float_zero_pred>()));
1537 EXPECT_TRUE(
1538 match(CSplatF32Zero, cstfp_pred_ty<always_true_pred<APFloat>>()));
1539 EXPECT_FALSE(
1540 match(CSplatF32Zero, cstfp_pred_ty<always_false_pred<APFloat>>()));
1541
1542 EXPECT_FALSE(match(CSplatF32Pi, cstfp_pred_ty<is_float_nan_pred>()));
1543 EXPECT_FALSE(match(CSplatF32Pi, cstfp_pred_ty<is_float_zero_pred>()));
1544 EXPECT_TRUE(match(CSplatF32Pi, cstfp_pred_ty<always_true_pred<APFloat>>()));
1545 EXPECT_FALSE(
1546 match(CSplatF32Pi, cstfp_pred_ty<always_false_pred<APFloat>>()));
1547 }

1550
1551 Constant *CMixedU32 = ConstantVector::get({CU32Max, CU32Zero, CU32DeadBeef});
1552 Constant *CU32Undef = UndefValue::get(U32Ty);
1553 Constant *CU32MaxWithUndef =
1554 ConstantVector::get({CU32Undef, CU32Max, CU32Undef});

1559 EXPECT_FALSE(match(CMixedU32, cst_pred_ty<always_false_pred<APInt>>()));

1562 EXPECT_FALSE(match(CU32MaxWithUndef, cst_pred_ty<is_unsigned_zero_pred>()));
1563 EXPECT_TRUE(match(CU32MaxWithUndef, cst_pred_ty<always_true_pred<APInt>>()));
1564 EXPECT_FALSE(
1565 match(CU32MaxWithUndef, cst_pred_ty<always_false_pred<APInt>>()));

1572 ConstantVector::get({CF32Undef, CF32NaN, CF32Undef});

1577 EXPECT_FALSE(match(CMixedF32, cstfp_pred_ty<always_false_pred<APFloat>>()));

1579 EXPECT_TRUE(match(CF32NaNWithUndef, cstfp_pred_ty<is_float_nan_pred>()));
1580 EXPECT_FALSE(match(CF32NaNWithUndef, cstfp_pred_ty<is_float_zero_pred>()));
1581 EXPECT_TRUE(
1582 match(CF32NaNWithUndef, cstfp_pred_ty<always_true_pred<APFloat>>()));

1587TEST_F(PatternMatchTest, InsertValue) {
1588 Type *StructTy = StructType::create(IRB.getContext(),
1589 {IRB.getInt32Ty(), IRB.getInt64Ty()});
1590 Value *Ins0 =
1591 IRB.CreateInsertValue(UndefValue::get(StructTy), IRB.getInt32(20), 0);
1592 Value *Ins1 = IRB.CreateInsertValue(Ins0, IRB.getInt64(90), 1);
1593
1594 EXPECT_TRUE(match(Ins0, m_InsertValue<0>(m_Value(), m_Value())));
1595 EXPECT_FALSE(match(Ins0, m_InsertValue<1>(m_Value(), m_Value())));
1596 EXPECT_FALSE(match(Ins1, m_InsertValue<0>(m_Value(), m_Value())));
1597 EXPECT_TRUE(match(Ins1, m_InsertValue<1>(m_Value(), m_Value())));
1598
1599 EXPECT_TRUE(match(Ins0, m_InsertValue<0>(m_Undef(), m_SpecificInt(20))));
1600 EXPECT_FALSE(match(Ins0, m_InsertValue<0>(m_Undef(), m_SpecificInt(0))));
1601
1602 EXPECT_TRUE(
1603 match(Ins1, m_InsertValue<1>(m_InsertValue<0>(m_Value(), m_Value()),
1604 m_SpecificInt(90))));
1605 EXPECT_FALSE(match(IRB.getInt64(99), m_InsertValue<0>(m_Value(), m_Value())));
1606}

1610typedef ::testing::Types<std::tuple<Value*, Instruction*>,
1611 std::tuple<const Value*, const Instruction *>>
1612 MutableConstTestTypes;
1613TYPED_TEST_CASE(MutableConstTest, MutableConstTestTypes);

1615TYPED_TEST(MutableConstTest, ICmp) {
1616 auto &IRB = PatternMatchTest::IRB;
1617
1618 typedef std::tuple_element_t<0, TypeParam> ValueType;
1619 typedef std::tuple_element_t<1, TypeParam> InstructionType;
1620
1621 Value *L = IRB.getInt32(1);
1622 Value *R = IRB.getInt32(2);
1623 ICmpInst::Predicate Pred = ICmpInst::ICMP_UGT;
1624
1625 ValueType MatchL;
1626 ValueType MatchR;
1627 ICmpInst::Predicate MatchPred;
1628
1629 EXPECT_TRUE(m_ICmp(MatchPred, m_Value(MatchL), m_Value(MatchR))
1630 .match((InstructionType)IRB.CreateICmp(Pred, L, R)));
1631 EXPECT_EQ(L, MatchL);
1632 EXPECT_EQ(R, MatchR);
1633}
